rue – it is only you who can grant your own wishes.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, Rowdy Buddha: The First Sapiens\n|\nBeneath hot sun, desert roses bloomed. Under cold moon, I still refused to.\n\n- Aspen Matis, Girl in the Woods: A Memoir\n|\nwhen you feel like hope is gone, look inside you and be strong and you'll finally see the truth- that hero lies in you.\n\n- Mariah\n|\nDo not swear by the moon, for she changes constantly. then your love would also change.\n\n- William Shakespeare, Romeo and Juliet\n|\nAnd then I did what I had never done in his presence, much less in his arms. I cried.\n\n- Erich Segal, Love Story\n|\nRead what you find interesting, and then follow your interests. You'll find that in doing so you always generate enough to illuminate the next step.\n\n- Mark Helprin, Freddy and Fredericka\n|\nThe whole point of being a good friend is being in the darkness. I’ll be your light, until you can be it yourself again.\n\n- Catherine Doyle, Inferno\n|\nWhen someone hurts you, hates you, don't hate him, win him with love; you will find the peace.\n\n- Debasish\n|\n... there was no need for him to hasten towards the attainment of a happiness already captured and held in a safe place, which would not escape his grasp again.\n\n- Marcel Proust, Swann's Way\n|\nEh, brother, but nature has to be corrected and guided, otherwise we'd all drown in prejudices. Without that there wouldn't be even a single great man.\n\n- Fyodor Dostoyevsky, Crime and Punishment\n|\nAll around us, birds woke up the sky.\n\n- Lauren Wolk, Wolf Hollow\n|\nDream, Dream DreamDreams transform into thoughts And thoughts result in action.\n\n- A.P.J.\n|\nAnd people who don’t dream, who don’t have any kind of imaginative life, they must… they must go nuts. I can’t imagine that.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nFriendship is selfless love, care, respect, and honor not a profitable opportunity.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nI closed my eyes and tried to sleep. But it was not until much later that I was able to get any real sleep. In a place far away from anyone or anywhere, I drifted off for a moment.\n\n- Haruki Murakami, The Wind-Up Bird Chronicle\n|\nI am writing in the garden. To write as one should of a garden one must write not outside it or merely somewhere near it, but in the garden.\n\n- Frances\n|\nHe was a gentle and sensitive soul, and therefore had a short temper, which is why he went straight after everything with an ax...\n\n- Bohumil Hrabal, I Served the King of England\n|\nWe may be helpless to stop bad things from happening, but perhaps God leaves us signs and road maps to help us recover and reconnect, provided we know where to look.\n\n- Jennifer Gardner Trulson, Where You Left Me\n|\nI always know what to expect of the things of Mother Earth. Sometimes they are cruel, but it is hard, clean cruelty. They don’t torture you with their own weakness.\n\n- Anna Lee Waldo, Sacajawea\n|\nViolence is a disease, a disease that corrupts all who use it regardless of the cause.\n\n- Chris\n|\nEnjoy being with yourself, you will then not feel alone.\n\n- Steven\n|\nThe purpose of writing is to hold a mirror to nature, but too much today is written from small mirrors in vanity cases.\n\n- John\n|\nIn eternity there is no time, only an instant long enough for a joke.\n\n- Hermann Hesse, Steppenwolf\n|\nNo woman marries for money; they are all clever enough, before marrying a millionaire, to fall in love with him first.\n\n- Cesare\n|\nA wise man, once he is past fifty, does not befuddle his senses with strong drink, nor make violent love in the cool spring night, nor dance on his hands.\n\n- Frans G. Bengtsson, The Long Ships\n|\nGod formed an alliance based on the world as it is, full of flaws, whereas prayer calls God to account for the world as it should be.\n\n- Philip Yancey, Prayer: Does It Make Any Difference?\n|\nWhen it is late, everyone cares!\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Six Words Inspiration\n|\nIf you tend to a flower, it will bloom, no matter how many weeds surround it.\n\